Re: Good enough


20 Jan 2020 17:18






I highly recommend that you read the rest of the series before jumping to that conclusion. All the characters, tech, and time travel shenanigans are previously established parts of Temporal Anomalies lore.

The tale series starts at SCP-2000 and several other mainlist entries not authored by me, including several Ad Astra Per Aspera skips which use Temporal Sinks as an FTL travel method. Thad Xyank and the Temporal Anomalies Department have a long arc behind them. I did my best to make this piece into something that could stand on its own but it seems that perhaps a little more context is needed for some. Check out the thad-xyank tag if you're interested in finding all of it.

Also I appreciate the criticism of  but the test audiences found that at the previous end-point, the narrative lacked a certain sense of resolution, which is why it was included. I'll take this under advisement, however. It may be worth it to leave that out or alter it in some way that leaves a bit more to the imagination.

Thanks.







